<rss version="2.0" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:ss="http://contenthub.aol.com/slideshow/"><channel><title><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></title><link/> https://www.engadget.com/ <description><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></description><language> en-US</language><copyright>版权所有雅虎 2023</copyright><pubDate> Wed, 05 Jul 2023 13:52:30 +0000</pubDate><generator>雅虎 http://yahoo.com </generator><item><title><![CDATA[Twitter quietly backtracks on requiring users to log in to see tweets]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>推特发布几天后<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-isnt-showing-tweets-unless-youre-logged-in-165254006.html">停止向注销用户显示推文</a></ins>，基本功能似乎正在回归。几位 Engadget 编辑再次能够在不登录帐户的情况下查看个人推文。然而，那些未登录的人的个人资料似乎仍然被破坏。例如，我可以看到用户的个人简介，但他们的推文提要没有显示。与此同时，<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/KLVNKBRWN/status/1676575665473089538">对于某些人来说，</a> iMessage 中的推文预览功能再次可用。</p><p> Twitter 所有者埃隆·马斯克 (Elon Musk) 表示，让注销用户无法访问推文是一项“临时紧急措施”。 “我们的数据遭到大量掠夺，导致普通用户的服务质量下降。”<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1674865731136020505">他写了。</a></ins></p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>该公司对于为何暂时关闭的原因也给出了类似的解释。<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-puts-strict-cap-on-how-many-tweets-users-can-read-each-day-182623928.html">设置限制</a></ins>每个用户每天能够阅读的推文数量。周二，<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-says-it-couldnt-tell-people-about-rate-limiting-in-advance-183928265.html">它说</a></ins>它做出了那个举动，<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitters-apps-are-breaking-following-elon-musks-decision-to-cap-tweet-rates-125028807.html">破坏了各种 Twitter 应用程序，</a></ins> “检测并消除损害平台的机器人和其他不良行为者”，例如那些正在抓取数据来训练人工智能模型的人。 Twitter 补充说，当时速率限制影响了一小部分用户。</p><p> Twitter 不再设有可供置评的通讯部门。尽管如此，公共推文再次可供任何人查看，就像 Meta 一样<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/metas-threads-is-already-showing-conversations-on-the-web-120453471.html">开始推出</a></ins>它的 Twitter 竞争对手是 Threads。该服务预计将在多个市场上线<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/metas-instagram-linked-twitter-rival-threads-could-arrive-on-july-6th-063129168.html">星期四</a></ins>， 但<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/metas-twitter-rival-threads-wont-initially-launch-in-the-eu-090314803.html">不在欧盟。</a></ins></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/twitter-quietly-backtracks-on-requiring-users-to-log-in-to-see-tweets-135230558.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/twitter-quietly-backtracks-on-requiring-users-to-log-in-to-see-tweets-135230558.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 7f8ab664-d44b-49ff-8ace-0a8aaf037b50</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 05 Jul 2023 13:52:30 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688565151</ingested><modified> 2023-07-05T13:52:33+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[Social & Online Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="2665" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-01/3a657cc0-a890-11ed-b679-512e51ea9b4a" width="4003"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]